HEADWORD: Sea saurian
<hw>Sea" sau"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any marine saurian; esp. <fld>(Paleon.)</fld>, the large extinct
species of <gen>Mosasaurus</gen>, <gen>Ichthyosaurus</gen>,
<gen>Plesiosaurus</gen>, and related genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seascape</ent>⟦br⟧
